# AI Ready Archive — environment configuration
#
# You normally DON'T need this file. On first run the app asks for your AI key
# IN THE BROWSER and saves it here for you (and you can change it any time from
# the "API key" button) — no hand-editing. This file is only for advanced or
# headless setups where you want to pre-seed the key.

# ─── Local AI key (the app writes this for you via the browser) ────
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# ─── Optional ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI_PROVIDER=anthropic       # leave unset to auto-detect from whichever key is set
# MODEL=claude-opus-4-7       # override the default model
# PORT=3000                   # override the HTTP port

# ─── Semantic search (embeddings) ──────────────────────────────────
# Internal archive search uses OpenAI embeddings (text-embedding-3-small). This
# key is SEPARATE from your chat key above — set it only if you want semantic
# search. Without it, search falls back to keyword/full-text (still useful, free).
# Online this is server-managed; locally it's optional.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# ─── Google Drive folder ingestion ─────────────────────────────────
# To pull articles from a shared Google Drive FOLDER, the Node uses the Drive API
# v3 with a Google API key (the folder must be shared "anyone with the link").
# No OAuth, no login. Online this is server-managed; locally it's optional —
# without it, paste individual article URLs instead.
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# ─── Hosted-only (set on the box, never in a local install) ────────
# When this Node runs online, the runtime supplies JWT_SECRET (must match the
# tracker), DATABASE_URL, and a shared ANTHROPIC_API_KEY. The box also carries the
# server-managed OPENAI_API_KEY (embeddings) and GOOGLE_API_KEY (Drive) above.
# You normally don't set any of these in a local install.
